<PubmedArticle><MedlineCitation Status="PubMed-not-MEDLINE" Owner="NLM"><PMID Version="1">41845757</PMID><DateRevised><Year>2026</Year><Month>03</Month><Day>18</Day></DateRevised><Article PubModel="Print"><Journal><ISSN IssnType="Electronic">1094-4087</ISSN><JournalIssue CitedMedium="Internet"><Volume>34</Volume><Issue>5</Issue><PubDate><Year>2026</Year><Month>Mar</Month><Day>09</Day></PubDate></JournalIssue><Title>Optics express</Title><ISOAbbreviation>Opt Express</ISOAbbreviation></Journal><ArticleTitle>Broadband achromatic silicon metalens integrated with silicon nitride waveguide across the RGB spectrum.</ArticleTitle><Pagination><StartPage>7916</StartPage><EndPage>7929</EndPage><MedlinePgn>7916-7929</MedlinePgn></Pagination><ELocationID EIdType="doi" ValidYN="Y">10.1364/OE.589874</ELocationID><Abstract><AbstractText>Metasurfaces integrated with photonic integrated circuits are essential for efficient guided-wave to free-space coupling. Conventional metalenses suffer from chromatic aberration in broadband visible systems. While recent studies have explored visible-band integration or achromatic designs separately, a waveguide-compatible achromatic metalens covering the full visible spectrum remains challenging. We propose and demonstrate a CMOS-compatible waveguide-integrated achromatic metalens operating across the RGB band under a compact aperture and moderate numerical aperture, designed via zone-multiplexed optimization with particle swarm optimization and detour phase modulation. Simulations show an average focal length of 32.53 <i>&#xb5;</i>m with only 2.78% variation, offering a scalable solution for on-chip optics applicable to AR/VR, spectrometers, and quantum photonics.</AbstractText></Abstract><AuthorList CompleteYN="Y"><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Qiu</LastName><ForeName>Zibing</ForeName><Initials>Z</Initials></Author><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Lin</LastName><ForeName>Yuhang</ForeName><Initials>Y</Initials></Author><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Zhou</LastName><ForeName>Xuanyu</ForeName><Initials>X</Initials></Author><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Zeng</LastName><ForeName>Jinjie</ForeName><Initials>J</Initials></Author><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Zhu</LastName><ForeName>Xiangyu</ForeName><Initials>X</Initials></Author><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Li</LastName><ForeName>Jiaqi</ForeName><Initials>J</Initials></Author><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Zhang</LastName><ForeName>Yanfeng</ForeName><Initials>Y</Initials></Author><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Wen</LastName><ForeName>Yuanhui</ForeName><Initials>Y</Initials></Author><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Yu</LastName><ForeName>Siyuan</ForeName><Initials>S</Initials></Author></AuthorList><Language>eng</Language><PublicationTypeList><PublicationType UI="D016428">Journal Article</PublicationType></PublicationTypeList></Article><MedlineJournalInfo><Country>United States</Country><MedlineTA>Opt Express</MedlineTA><NlmUniqueID>101137103</NlmUniqueID><ISSNLinking>1094-4087</ISSNLinking></MedlineJournalInfo><CitationSubset>IM</CitationSubset></MedlineCitation><PubmedData><History><PubMedPubDate PubStatus="medline"><Year>2026</Year><Month>3</Month><Day>18</Day><Hour>7</Hour><Minute>26</Minute></PubMedPubDate><PubMedPubDate PubStatus="pubmed"><Year>2026</Year><Month>3</Month><Day>18</Day><Hour>7</Hour><Minute>25</Minute></PubMedPubDate><PubMedPubDate PubStatus="entrez"><Year>2026</Year><Month>3</Month><Day>18</Day><Hour>1</Hour><Minute>2</Minute></PubMedPubDate></History><PublicationStatus>ppublish</PublicationStatus><ArticleIdList><ArticleId IdType="pubmed">41845757</ArticleId><ArticleId IdType="doi">10.1364/OE.589874</ArticleId><ArticleId IdType="pii">588938</ArticleId></ArticleIdList></PubmedData></PubmedArticle></PubmedArticleSet>